Handle change in /experiments/ API

The /experiments/ endpoint no longer returns an array, protecting us
from the following JSON vulnerability:
https://haacked.com/archive/2008/11/20/anatomy-of-a-subtle-json-vulnerability.aspx/

See this corresponding commit in the mock API:
https://github.com/openjck/firefox-test-tube-mock-api/commit/806a27d152f0434d2a2931ace3877668e24fbc82

Fix #13: Add favicon

This icon is a modification of the following icon from Icons8:
https://icons8.com/icon/19729/thin-test-tube

Their icons are free without attribution for popular open-source
projects, which they define as projects with a community of users and
contributors:
https://icons8.com/license
https://icons8.com/articles/weve-contributed-an-icon-to-imageoptim/

Their definition of "popular" isn't perfectly precise, but I would hope
that any open-source project at Mozilla would qualify. And this is a
modification of an icon as it is.

Do show chart animations for overlay

I disabled animations in the overlay because I thought it was overkill.
If a user chooses to make a chart fullscreen, they don't need to see the
animation all over again.

But the animation setting also applies to the animation that is run when
a population is enabled or disabled. There doesn't appear to be a way to
animate one of these events but not the other, so I'd rather animate
them both.

Fix #1: Paginate the tables on the homepage

I decided to remove sorting as part of this. I had it working at one
point, but the user experience of sorting while also paginating was
really weird. I imagine most people would have been confused by it.

I don't think sorting is as useful when pagination is possible and
experiments are reverse-sorted by start date. And if there are cases
where someone really wants to find an experiment by name, search would
probably be a better way of doing that.

Move front-end to repository root

As an obsessively organized person this sort of kills me. But there's no
other way around it other than splitting the front-end into its own
repository, which we decided not to do.

Greenkeeper and create-react-app-buildpack both insist that package.json
be at the root of the repository. react-scripts insists that
package.json be in the same directory as the src and public directories.
(And it's not possible to rename them, either.)

So we're stuck with weirdly-named src and public folders at the root of
the repository. Oh well.

Move front-end files back

Temporarily move front-end files back to the frontend directory,
essentially reverting f722c1373805288b6b4fcd1ee7e802688eac3124. The npm
scripts don't work when package.json is at the root of the repo.

root.

Merge pull request #73 from openjck/no-more-weird-this-binding

Use arrow functions to forego weird this binding

Turn off chart animations

Chart animations can be distracting. They are triggered whenever a chart
is rendered, meaning that animations happen whenever charts are updated,
whenever a user performs a search, and more.

The animations that play when the populations are changed can be useful,
but unfortunately there doesn't appear to be a way to enable *only*
those animations.
